  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> basmati rice</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>lean pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) and <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> harissa lean pork mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684852756120-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684852756120-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684852756120-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684852756120-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684852756120-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>harissa lean pork mixture</strong> and cook for 4 min or until it’s beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Cook for a further 4 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684852759834-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
